headline: How The Narrative Around High Liner Foods (TSX:HLF) Is Shifting After Q3 And The USDA Deal
summary: Why the Fair Value Estimate Has Barely Moved The fair value estimate for High Liner Foods now sits at about CA$18.09, compared with CA$18.03 previously, a tiny shift that reflects only a very slight adjustment to the valuation model. This small move lines up with mixed sentiment, where the new USDA contract supports the revenue outlook while more cautious assumptions on broader volumes and a trimmed C$16 price target signal a more balanced view after weaker Q3 results. Stay tuned to see how...
